Great ball, great decision to review.

commentary: de Silva to Fakhar Zaman, OUT taken at mid-off! Hasaranga gets his revenge! Tosses this one fuller and closer to Fakhar's swing. He hit him wide of mid-off last over when there was more width. This time he's forced to drive from inside the line and he ends up getting it off the low part of the outside half. Bat swivels in his hands and this floats seductively to Udana's right. He follows the path and puts something of a slow-mo dive to grab onto a well-judged catch

This time he's forced to drive from inside the line and he ends up getting it off the low part of the outside half. Bat swivels in his hands and this floats seductively to Udana's right. commentary: Pradeep to Babar Azam, OUT mix up and Haris Sohail has to go!. This was a length ball outside off, Babar tried to flick, it took an inside edge and flicked his pad and rolled away towards slip. Sohail wanted a single and was charging down the track, Babar was never interested and/or aware of what his partner was doing till he belatedly sent him back. The throw was relayed to the bowler and he took out the stumps from a yard away with Sohail well short

commentary: Udana to Imad Wasim, OUT the strangulation works. Pakistan weren't getting the ball away, and Imad saw a normal pace delivery and went for it. It was not the easiest to hit, back of a length outside off and his slash ends up as a top edge that loops to deep point, where it's safely held.

commentary: Udana to Wahab Riaz, 2 runs dropped by Pradeep at short fine leg. Wahab is standing almost square on and Udana bowls it short and on the stumps, he gets inside the line to try and paddle-pull it over short fine, doesn't get hold of it. The ball is not travelling too fast but it's to Pradeep's right. Did he need to dive to get it? Perhaps not, but he does it and it bounces out of his hands

commentary: Usman Shinwari to Jayasuriya, OUT got him? Yes! A faint edge! It's not to be for Shehan Jayasuriya. He's looking at the heavens in despair. What a knock. Just not enough to best Pakistan's best bowler on the night. Length all angled into the corridor. Opens the face and wants to run this down to third man but gets a faint edge that carries to the keeper. A standing ovation as he goes off. He's doubled his ODI tally today with his first fifty. Won't forget this for a long time

commentary: Shadab Khan to Shanaka, OUT finds deep midwicket! In three balls, a potential miracle has been seriously dented. That's a terrible delivery if you ask anyone, including the bowler himself. Very short on off stump. Backs away and looks to pull this over the midwicket boundary. It comes off the toe-end and Fakhar runs in, lunges and slides with grace as he holds on to this. Shanaka kept the scoring rate ticking early on and barely did anything wrong this evening. But he won't be there at the end for Sri Lanka either

commentary: Wahab Riaz to de Silva, FOUR runs wow! What is with this guy and hitting over extra cover? Some stunning inside-out hits. This one is a slower ball at a length outside off. He waits on it, plants half a stride out and slaps this over the infielder

commentary: Wahab Riaz to Kumara, OUT and he's bluffed him comprehensively! Oh Wahab, why'd you do that to the poor No. 10. Bowls it short of a length. Kumara is fending for a bouncer because of that field change. He's trapped right in front of the stumps, on the knee flap, as this slides on from the surface. They don't have any reviews left, but Kumara doesn't look too livid about this so we could assume there's no bat on it

commentary: Shadab Khan to de Silva, OUT taken at deep midwicket. And that is the end. Full ball outside off, there for one of his favoured inside-out lofted drives, but he chooses to go slog sweep. He's got no room to execute it after shuffling into the off side. Ends up slicing it for Ifthikar who runs in some ten yards and holds on easily
